Besides our excellent keynote speakers, out of the submitted papers to main track and workshops,
we selected about 230 high-quality papers for presentation at the conference and publication in the
proceedings, published by Elsevier in their Procedia Computer Science series. Submission was very
competitive this year and the main track accepted 64 papers from 184 submissions (34% acceptance
rate)
ICCS relies strongly on the vital contributions of our workshop organizers to attract high quality
papers in many subject areas. We would like to thank all committee members for the main track and
the workshops for their contribution to ensure a high standard for the accepted papers. As per every
year we would like to thank Elsevier, the conference is organized with their financial and
administrative support.
We are proud to note that ICCS is an ERA 2010 A-ranked conference series.
We wish you a successful and enjoyable conference in Cairns.
June 2014
